{"name":"Insomnia","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You are unable to sleep, or unable to sleep for an extended period of time. Ths is most often due to anxiety or depression and the accompanying negative thought patterns. Insomniacs may find themselves nodding of at inopportune times, but never for long. As a result, they are frequently lethargic, inattentive, and irritable.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alienation, responsibility overload, the unknown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You have a near total inability to find rest in sleep when it is desired. Treat long recharges as short recharges, or do not receive any recharge benefis at all.","id":"6d58wn9yr5"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skill","skillType":"perceive"}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"caqbphr2zo"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"allActions"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"ur7b3bsnvm"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0uJyO8rR1JgNzQgg"}
{"name":"Neural Damage","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You suffered some type of neurological damage that cannot yet be cured. The affliction is part of your ego and remains even when resleeving. This damage may have been inherited, resulted from a poorly designed morph or implant, or inflicted by a nanovirus during the Fall. Work with your GM to agree on a specific disorder appropriate to your game. The GM may inflict impairment modifiers (usually &ndash;10) as appropriate, according to the affliction.<br />This trait may be taken multiple times, for different afflictions.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 79","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You have an inability to make or understand music. Automatically fail music-related skill tests.","id":"gntwumq9jh"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"Amusica","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fNDiX4wH5sOogDSv"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1MFYOJDsC6fXjZs6"}
{"name":"Anxiety","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>With general anxiety disorder, you are overcome with worry about nearly everything. Even simple tasks represent the potential for failure on a catastrophic scale and should be avoided or minimized. Negative outcomes are always assumed to be the only possibility.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Bad news, boredom, helplessness, the unkown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You must be convinced with a Persuade or Provoke Test to do almost anything, and even then will self-sabotage or give up after a short time.","id":"3bwe0bs9aw"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ikPQVGv3PoEKNsVo"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2mzr3RJg79AhS9P1"}
{"name":"Body Dysmorphia","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You believe that you are irrevocably ugly or defective, making you unable to interact with others or function normally for fear of ridicule and humiliation. You are secretive and reluctant to seek help because you are afraid others will think you vain. A similar disorder, gender dysphoria, occurs when your sexual biology conflcts with your internal gender identity. Due to resleeving, both disorders are fairly common. Some asyncs have a similar species dysmorphia disorder, where they become convinced they are aliens trapped in transhuman forms; they often seek out exotic morphs and modifiations.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alienation, helplessness, resleeving","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"special","test":"resleevingStress"}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"4f5spsz9l5"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CB9xcF5SFGZuXpo8"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5bYY1HUbtkd4qCA1"}
{"name":"Fugue","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You enter a fugue state where you display little attention to external stimuli. You still function physiologically but refrain from speaking and stare of into the distance, unable to focus on events around you.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Helplessness, the unkown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You are totally non-responsive to most stimuli. You will walk only if led by a helper. You will not even defend yourself if attacked, simply curling into a fetal position if physically assaulted.","id":"s0n0wts7zu"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6fZdQiCVVPWo3b57"}
{"name":"Autophagy","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Ths anxiety disorder, characterized by self-cannibalism of the limbs, usually only occurs among neo-octopi.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alienation, injury, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You must make a successful WIL Check or begin to consume one of your limbs.","id":"1w0ji5pn4l"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SYN8FACmFn8iNEdW"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8hj7b97BoSCNRAOk"}
{"name":"Reiterative Schizophrenia","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Not to be confused with the genetic disorder, reiterative schizophrenia has similar symptoms but develops in egos that undergo frequent resleeving, possibly due to some sort of repetitive error in the download process. Schizophrenics lose their ability to discern reality from unreality. You experience delusions, hallucinations (often in support of the delusions), and fragmented or disorganized speech. You experience your behavior as perfectly normal, to the point of becoming paranoid that others are involved in a grand deception.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alienation, drug use, forking, the unknown","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You experience delusions and hallucinations as determined by the GM and are prone to conspiratorial thinking.","id":"y83gfm72t9"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"allActions"}],"modifier":-20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"the test requires coherent communication","id":"tuxtxp4tz1"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HWQka8bnCQNWIsOH"}
{"name":"Disassociative Personality Disorder","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>A separate, distinct personality develops apart from your original personality. The personalities may or may not be aware of each other and &ldquo;conscious&rdquo; during the actions of the other personality, though there is some basic information sharing (such as language and core skill sets). Most subjects have only a single extra personality, but it is not unheard of to have several personalities. Each personality sees itself as a distinct person with their own wants, needs, and motivations.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Helplessness, specific memories, the unkown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"The other personality must be roleplayed (perhaps by the GM or another player)","id":"sdashh9x11"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HzdG7uvC6S9ksXii"}
{"name":"Depression","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Clinical depression is characterized by intense feelings of hopelessness and worthlessness. You feel as though nothing you do matters and no one cares anyway. You find it difficult to be motivated; even simple acts such as eating and bathing seem monumental.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alienation, grief, helplessness, life transitions, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"action","action":"task","subtype":""}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"ooom67mugp"},{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"Make a WIL Check to take any sort of action","id":"2ehteua1jp"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JeEbUnocwrSmBRbv"}
{"name":"Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD)","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>ADHD is the inability to notice details and focus on any one task for an extended period. You may find yourself starting multiple tasks, beginning a new one after only a cursory attempt at the prior task. You may also have a manic edge that manifests as confience in your ability to get a job done, even though you will quickly lose all interest in it.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Overstimulation, sleep deprivation, the unknown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skill","skillType":"perceive"},{"type":"action","action":"task","subtype":""}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"qvpxavzosu"},{"type":"duration","subtype":"taskActionTimeframe","modifier":50,"taskType":"","halve":false,"id":"y4ltfs02lk"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hmAB5ZRLlBwzoNCN"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KGVazYoSVghW6s9D"}
{"name":"Conversion Disorder","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You suffer a neurological condition such as blindness, deafness, inability to speak, loss of balance, seizures, or paralysis in high-stress situations. Some asyncs suffer from a similar condition, alien sensory disorder, where attempts to use phantom alien sensory organs disrupt one or more of their actual physical senses.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alienation, the unkown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"WIL Check or suffer from one of the chosen conditions.","id":"htbwlmakn4"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8bkbQsPN3CVNWXG"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KRtLAVug932mimDb"}
