{"name":"Narcissistic Personality Disorder","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You believe yourself to be the single most important person in the universe. Nothing else takes precedence and everything must be done according to your whim. Failure to comply with your dictates will incite rage and physical assault.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Criticism, insults, praise, the unknown","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You demand attention. You may be provoked to violence if insulted or if others fail to comply with your demands (WIL Check). Narcissistic NPCs are immune to Persuade Tests.","id":"74fhieu1fg"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skill","skillType":"persuade"}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"qs5srpix94"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZsQ97zoDekasiJIK"}
{"name":"Impulse Control Disorder","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You must engage in one specific activity that dominates your thoughts: compulsive shopping, explosive aggressiveness, kleptomania, mesh addiction, pyromania, sexual exhibitionism, etc. You feel a sense of building anxiety when prevented from engaging in this behavior for an extended period (usually several times a day to weekly, depending on the impulse) and will often engage in this behavior at inconvenient or inappropriate times.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Helplessness, impulse focus, the unkown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You must make a WIL Check not to engage in the impulsive activity. If denied the activity for too long, you suffer modifirs between –10 and –30.","id":"4ii3hlyly4"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"evAjbeZyarFnOnjD"}
{"name":"Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>PTSD results from life-threatening incidents. You develop an acute fixation on what happened, obsessively reliving the past, losing sleep, suffering anxiety and depression, and becoming easily angered or irritated. PTSD survivors will avoid painful memories and suffer extreme anxiety if forced into similar circumstances.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Frustration, helplessness, pain, specific memories, the unknown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"WIL Check to avoid responding to imagined threats based on the traumatic experience with violence. Otherwise treat as anxiety, depression, or phobia as appropriate.","id":"5591hzwmlr"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"f0Srg1EIgM6CyeJA"}
{"name":"Alien Behavior Disorder","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Ths disorder primarily affects asyncs. You experience strange urges to behave in an alien fashion or to use phantom appendages or other body parts that don&rsquo;t map to your transhuman form.<br /><br /></p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alienation, exsurgents, the unknown","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You must make a WIL Check or be compelled to exhibit alien behavior. The compulsion examples listed on the Inflence Effect tables ▶278 provide a number of possibilities.","id":"sdidpcnmo9"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.LaYIo7Zt4VdcFSYd"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jPVM8JvE0NLw3cZ1"}
{"name":"Neural Damage","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You have difficulty ascertaining distance.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You suffered some type of neurological damage that cannot yet be cured. The affliction is part of your ego and remains even when resleeving. This damage may have been inherited, resulted from a poorly designed morph or implant, or inflicted by a nanovirus during the Fall. Work with your GM to agree on a specific disorder appropriate to your game. The GM may inflict impairment modifiers (usually &ndash;10) as appropriate, according to the affliction.<br />This trait may be taken multiple times, for different afflictions.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 79","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"ranged","negativeRangeModifiersMultiplier":2,"id":"0206qe1vn4"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"Lack Depth Perception","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fNDiX4wH5sOogDSv"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kmcDHps4GNpMdq5M"}
{"name":"Phobia","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You have an irrational fear of a particular place, situation, or thing. Common phobias include AIs, microgravity, pandora gates, muses, robots, enclosed spaces, open spaces, and death.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Helplessness, phobia focus","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"Make a WIL Check to enter the proximity of the phobia’s focus. If exposed to the focus, make a WIL Check or flee. Suffer –10 to –30 in the focus’s presence.","id":"9r3tqy5sji"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oWIjaq0qdJcz4WU9"}
{"name":"Paranoia","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You mistrust others. You are hypervigilant but also hypersensitive to perceived hostility and insults. You bear grudges for longer periods.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 225","restrictions":"","triggers":"Betrayal, conspiratorial behavior, the unknown, violence","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skill","skillType":"kinesics"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"1lod709b70"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"sav"}],"modifier":20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"is an NPC and against Persuade","id":"wbkm1pdkce"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"sav"}],"modifier":-20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"is an NPC and against hostile Provoke Tests","id":"ic2ybxsfmz"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ri4FOaqxsl3hYaBh"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tvqTsb6DYfmr2YX6"}
{"name":"Cosmic Anxiety Disorder","permission":{"default":0,"qJl17WpEHiovQQBC":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>This disorder arises from facing x-risks, aliens, and incomprehensibly advanced technology. It functions much like anxiety; you are helpless in the face of an uncaring and dangerous universe.<br /><br /></p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 224","restrictions":"","triggers":"Alien/TITAN technology, the unknown, x-risks","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"Like anxiety, but when faced with an alien or TITAN threat, make a WIL Check or either flee or collapse in panic.","id":"ofp8kd42tu"}],"id":"_defaultLevel"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.LO0lcmmFwALif0eN"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"v19jkjnXIP2PwKFl"}
